| Main Path                                                          | <p>**Thought**</p><p></p><p>Puja services offer individuals a way to engage in spiritual practices from the comfort of their homes or preferred locations. ONDC is committed to making these services interoperable, ensuring easy access and availability of various Pujas to cater to diverse spiritual needs.</p><p></p><p>**Initiate Buyer’s Request**</p><p></p><p>1. Buyer’s request for any Spirituality related product can be raised through the buyer app in three possible ways:</p><p>&emsp;a. Search through category: Buyer can easily search for the category directly such as Puja Services</p><p>&emsp;b. Search by city: Buyer app can raise a search request by city for eg. all sellers selling only in Lucknow</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. This search can be specific to fulfilment type ie. buyer fulfilled service or seller fulfilled service that the seller can define at the time of sending across the catalogue and the buyer can choose based on the options available for their location.</p><p>2. For explanation purposes, search by category is defined here.</p><p>&emsp;a. Search by category</p><p>1. Buyer on the buyer app raises an intent to purchase a spirituality service of either of the following, </p><p>&emsp;a. Puja Services</p><p>&emsp;b. Astrology Services</p><p>2. The buyer can raise an intent of either one of the above or all of the above categories of spirituality services available</p><p></p><p>**Broadcast to Sellers**</p><p>1. The interest is broadcasted to all the available sellers in the specific domain on the ONDC network via the gateway</p><p></p><p>**Seller responds with their catalogue**</p><p></p><p>1. Sellers will respond with their catalogues with **attributes** for the buyer app to define the discovery experience for the buyer. These attributes will be needed as selection from the buyer to define the quote of a purchasable item. The different attributes defined are:</p><p>&emsp;a. Name of Pooja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Specify the name of Puja eg. Maha Mritunjay Path</p><p>&emsp;b. Capacity for the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. How many people would be attending the Puja. Let’s say a single person, or a couple or a complete family of 4 people or more people</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. This will be defined from the seller’s end. Possible values for the attribute can be single person, a couple or family of two, family of four and so on. </p><p>&emsp;c. Slots available</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers will respond with the available slots which can specify date, time and service for the Puja. For example Maha Mritunjay Puja can be performed on 6th October from 4pm to 6pm</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Date of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. Time of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;d. Duration of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. How long the Puja will take place for? </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Duration of subscription: The duration will be defined in the ISO format to enable a user to specify and answer- how long any particular subscription is needed for?</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. P is the duration designator (for period) placed at the start of the duration representation. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. Y is the year designator that follows the value for the number of years.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;4. M is the month designator that follows the value for the number of months.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;5. W is the week designator that follows the value for the number of weeks. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;6. D is the day designator that follows the value for the number of days.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;7. T is the time designator that precedes the time components of the representation.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;a. 1 month duration can be presented as **P1M**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;b. 48 hours duration can be presented as **PT48H**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;c. 6 months duration can be presented as **P6M**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Location of Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. The seller will define the available locations for the Puja according to their catalogue</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Seller defined location: Puja being performed at the temple</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. Buyer defined location: Seller provides the option to the buyer to choose the location. For eg. buyer’s home</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. In case the Puja is being performed at the Temple, Temple details will be mentioned as Temple Description. </p><p>&emsp;e. Fulfilment type</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Online Puja: the Puja would be attended by the user in an online setup over a video call. Seller can send this as a part of the catalogue if the same service is offered by the seller</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Offline Puja: Where there is location selection for puja offline, be it the seller’s location(Temple) or Pujari specified location or buyer specified location</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Buyer fulfilled service: Seller can provide the option of buyer choosing the location</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. Seller fulfilled service: Puja being performed at the temple</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. Both online and offline Puja: Where the seller can offer services at the location of the seller/buyer and also send the video of the puja after completion</p><p>&emsp;f. Add ons</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Add-ons such as a Potli or some Yantra which would be provided along with the Puja can be specified in this attribute. These will be paid add ons and would have a monetary value attached to it.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. There can also be free add ons as a consultation astrology paper that is being provided free of cost along with the service</p><p></p><p>2. Other attributes for sending the detailed catalogue for the buyer app to create the right experience for the buyer will be as below.</p><p>&emsp;a. Service or Concern: </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with Service or Concern to specify the type of Puja services they offer, such as career related Puja or Relationship Related Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. These will be enums as defined below:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Career</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. Marriage</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. Love</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;4. Energy</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;5. Home</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;6. Education</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;7. Job</p><p>&emsp;b. Pujari for the Puja: </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with a list of Pujaris based on their </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Specialties that the Pujari supports</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. Seller defined ratings and </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. Experience of the Pujari</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;4. Certifications available for the Pujari</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Pujari’s photo can also be passed as an added attribute for the buyer to take an informed decision</p><p>&emsp;c. Language of Pujari:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with languages that the Pandit speaks based on preferred languages (e.g., Hindi, English, Kannada)</p><p>&emsp;d. Experience of Pujari:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with the experience level of each Pandit, helping them select a knowledgeable professional. This can be in years eg. 10+ years, 12+ years</p><p>&emsp;e. Education/Qualification of Pujari:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Any eligibility certification can be specified for this attribute</p><p>&emsp;f. Form for User Details:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. A form to collect necessary user information can be shared by the seller (e.g., name, contact number, birth details, Gotra)</p><p>&emsp;g. Image of Pooja: This can also be passed as a part of seller’s catalogue</p><p>&emsp;h. Description of Puja: </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Any further details related to the Puja that the seller deems fit for the user to be aware of can be passed in this attribute. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. For eg. for Rin Mukti Puja: A very remarkable and beneficial Puja to remove all debts is held in Ujjain's ancient Rinmukteshwar Mahadev Temple. In this worship, yellow objects are offered to Mahadev. According to history, during the Satayuga period, King Harishchandra himself performed this ritual in order to pay off his debts. </p><p>&emsp;i. Credentials of Poojari</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Any certificates that the Seller app understands are important to verify the authenticity for the seller can be added for this attribute</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Certificate name</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. Certification number to check the authenticity</p><p>&emsp;j. Rating from seller</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Seller can pass the rating related to the any puja so that the buyer can take an informed decision regarding the same</p><p>&emsp;k. Checklist for the Puja: The seller can also send a checklist as part of the Puja. For eg. if a Puja has to be done at an individual’s home, Gangajal, Janeyu can be some specific items that need to be available for the Puja</p><p></p><p>**Offer Management & Selection**</p><p>1. Buyer will select the most suitable puja that they deem fit for their usage from all seller Apps catalogue</p><p>2. Different models to be present for selection as received in the catalogue sent by the seller.</p><p>&emsp;a. Scenario 1: **Offline fulfilment model**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Let’s suppose the seller app offers offline consumption of Puja ie. Puja being held at either the seller’s location(Temple) or buyer’s location(Home)</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. The buyer app will have to provide details related to the selection for the seller to provide a quote. This will include</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. Offline Puja: Where there is location selection for puja offline, be it the seller’s location(Temple) or Pujari specified location or buyer specified location</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Buyer fulfilled puja: Pujari visiting home for Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Seller fulfilled puja: Buyer visiting the temple for Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iv. Name of Pooja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Specify the name of Puja eg. Maha Mritunjay Path</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;v. Capacity for the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● How many people would be attending the Puja. Let’s say a single person, or a couple or a complete family of 4 people or more people</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;vi. Slots available</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Sellers can respond with the available slots which can specify date and time for the Puja. For example Maha Mritunjay Puja can be performed on 6th October from 4pm to 6pm</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Date of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Time of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;vii. Duration of subscription: The duration will be defined in the ISO format to enable a user to specify and answer- how long any particular subscription is needed for?</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● P is the duration designator (for period) placed at the start of the duration representation. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Y is the year designator that follows the value for the number of years.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● M is the month designator that follows the value for the number of months.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● W is the week designator that follows the value for the number of weeks. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● D is the day designator that follows the value for the number of days.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● T is the time designator that precedes the time components of the representation.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;a. 1 month duration can be presented as **P1M**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;b. 48 hours duration can be presented as **PT48H**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;c. 6 months duration can be presented as **P6M**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;viii. Fulfilment type</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Online Puja: the Puja would be attended by the user in an online setup over a video call. Seller can send this as a part of the catalogue if the same service is offered by the seller</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Offline Puja: </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;a. Seller fulfilled Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;i. In case the Puja is being performed at the Temple, Temple details can be mentioned as Temple Description</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;b. Buyer fulfilled Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;i. Location of Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. The puja can be performed at the user provided address</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ix. Add ons</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Add-ons such as a Potli or some Yantra which would be provided along with the Puja can be specified in this attribute. These will be paid add ons and would have a value attached to it.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● There can also be free add ons as a consultation astrology paper that is being provided free of cost along with the service</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;x. Pincode: Conditional mandatory (will be provided for offline model at the buyer location)</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;xi. The seller app will in return provide the quotation of the product as selected by the buyer</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● The best price available for the product selection</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● if the chosen product for purchase is available or not</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;xii. Breakup of best offer price</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Discounted base price/Base price</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Taxes involved</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Convenience fee(if any)</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Discount applied(if any)</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Other charges(if any)</p><p>&emsp;b. Scenario 2: **Online model**</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Name of Pooja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Specify the name of Puja eg. Maha Mritunjay Path</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Slots available</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Sellers can respond with the available slots which can specify date, time and duration for the Puja. For example Maha Mritunjay Puja can be performed on 6th October from 4pm to 6pm</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Date of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Time of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. Duration of the Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● How long the Puja will take place for? This will be defined in hours for eg. Maha Mritunjay Puja for two days will be defined as 48 hours</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iv. Add ons</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Add-ons such as a Potli or some Yantra which would be provided along with the Puja can be specified in this attribute. These will be paid add ons and would have a value attached to it.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● There can also be free add ons as a consultation astrology paper that is being provided free of cost along with the service</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;v. Pincode: Conditional mandatory (in case add ons need to be delivered at the buyer’s address)</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;vi. The seller app will in return provide the quotation of the product as selected by the buyer</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● The best price available for the product selection</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● if the chosen product for purchase is available or not</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;vii. Breakup of best offer price</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Discounted base price/Base price</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Taxes involved</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Convenience fee(if any)</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Discount applied(if any)</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;● Other charges(if any)</p><p></p><p>3. The next step would be to place the order and agree to the terms of agreement by both seller and buyer app</p><p>4. Pass the user identifier along with the address while the order is being placed to the seller app</p><p></p><p></p><p>**Payment and Confirmation of Order**</p><p></p><p>1. The buyer will make the payment to confirm the order</p><p>&emsp;a. Payment can have three scenarios: </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Entire payment to be made pre-fulfilment. In this case the payment needs to be made before the order is placed. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Entire payment to be made post-fulfilment. In this case the payment needs to be made post the order is placed and puja service delivered delivered</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. Entire payment to be made on-fulfilment</p><p>&emsp;b. Payment can be collected by both the buyer and seller app</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Buyer app collecting payment:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Buyer app will send the payment link to the buyer and collect payment</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. Buyer app to send details for confirming order to the seller app depending on the method of payment</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;a. Puja chosen details according to the select call</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;b. transaction ID</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;c. User Identifier: Phone number or email</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. Once confirmed from the seller app, the Puja purchase would be mapped to the user</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Seller app collecting payment:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. While the seller app sends the terms of agreement for the sale to go through, the seller app will also provide the payment link along with the cancellation terms</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. The buyer will make payment through the same link and order ID would be generated by the seller app</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. The seller app will pass the order ID to the buyer app</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;4. Post this the buyer app will map the Puja details to the user and save the same on the profile for the user</p><p></p><p>**Post Order activities**</p><p></p><p>1. Once the order is confirmed, the buyer and seller will take relevant actions as per the terms of the order</p><p>&emsp;a. All the steps to be taken to provide the service of the Puja will be done at the seller app’s end. The buyer app has to maintain only the status of the order to provide the buyer an informed decision about the updates for his purchase</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Puja details to be visible to the user on Buyer Platform under the user profile section</p><p>2. In case the Puja is being delivered online/offline on different dates, below scenarios are possible.</p><p></p><p>a. Scenario 1: Fulfilment Type- Offline Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Seller app which is taking care of delivery(both online and offline) which is in this case is offline delivery of service of Puja, needs to update buyer app for keeping track of the service</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. This call can have 3 statuses for order</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Accepted: Once the seller app accepts the order</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. In- Progress: Puja service is in progress</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. Completed: When the Puja service order is completed</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. As and when actual delivery is completed for the Puja service ,seller app to send completed to mark the delivery completion of the puja service</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iv. On the other hand, a user can also request for status of the product. In this case, buyer app to send a /status call and receive the /on_status from seller app to inform the user</p><p></p> |
| **Alternate Path**                                                 | <p>In case the payment fails on the seller app, below use cases are possible in that case:</p><p></p><p></p><p>Use case 1 - Redirection and timed out</p><p>1. When the seller app is collecting the payment and there happens to be a payment failure at the seller app’s end:</p><p>&emsp;a. | Main Path                                                                                           | <p>**Thought**</p><p></p><p>Astrology services offer valuable guidance and insights into various aspects of life, including career, relationships, and personal well-being. By utilising the wisdom of astrology, individuals can make more informed decisions and find clarity in challenging situations. ONDC is working to make astrology services interoperable across its network, ensuring that users have seamless access to trusted astrologers, regardless of their platform, and can benefit from personalised consultations to meet their unique needs.</p><p></p><p>**Initiate Buyer’s Request**</p><p></p><p>1. Buyer’s request for any Spirituality related product can be raised through the buyer app in three possible ways:</p><p>&emsp;a. Search through category: Buyer can easily search for the category directly such as Astrology service</p><p>&emsp;b. Search by city: Buyer app can raise a search request by city for eg. all sellers selling only in Lucknow</p><p>2. For explanation purposes, search by category is defined here.</p><p>&emsp;a. Search by category: Buyer on the buyer app raises an intent to purchase an astrology service of either of the following, </p><p>&emsp;a. Astrology Services</p><p>&emsp;b. Puja Services</p><p></p><p>The buyer can raise an intent of either one of the above or all of the above categories of spirituality services available</p><p></p><p>**Broadcast to Sellers**</p><p></p><p>The interest is broadcasted to all the available sellers in the specific domain on the ONDC network via the gateway</p><p></p><p>**Seller responds with their catalogue**</p><p></p><p>1. Sellers will respond with their catalogues with **attributes** for the buyer app to define the discovery experience for the buyer. These attributes will be needed as selection from the buyer to define the quote of a purchasable item. The different attributes defined are:</p><p>&emsp;a. Service or Concern: </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with Service or Concern to specify the type of E Puja services they offer, such as career related Puja or Relationship Related Puja</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. These will be enums as defined below:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. Career</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;2. Marriage</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. Love</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;4. Energy</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;5. Home</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;6. Education</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;7. Job</p><p>&emsp;b. Astrologer for the consultation: </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with a list of astrologers based on their specialties, ratings, and experience.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Astrologer’s photo can also be passed as an added attribute for the buyer to take an informed decision</p><p>&emsp;c. Language of Astrologer:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with languages that the Pandit speaks based on preferred languages (e.g., Hindi, English, Kannada)</p><p>&emsp;d. Experience of Astrologer:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Sellers can respond with the experience level of each Astrologer, helping them select a knowledgeable professional. This can be in years eg. 10+ years, 12+ years</p><p>&emsp;e. Education/Qualification of Astrologer:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Any eligibility certification can be specified for this attribute</p><p>&emsp;f. Slots available: Sellers will respond with available slots which can specify date and time. For example, call consultation with Dr. Ajai Bhambi costs Rs.500 on 15th Oct at 6PM</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Date of astro consult</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Time of astro consult</p><p>&emsp;g. Form for User Details:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. A form to collect necessary user information can be shared by the seller (e.g., name, contact number, birth details, Gotra)</p><p>&emsp;h. Fulfilment type</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Chat consultation: Where the astrologer consults on chat with the buyer</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Call consultation: Where the astrologer consults on call with the buyer</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. Video consultation: Where the astrologer consults on a video call with the buyer</p><p>&emsp;i. Add ons:</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Add-ons such as a Potli or some Yantra which would be provided along with the Puja can be specified in this attribute. Call consultation: Where the astrologer consults on call with the buyer app, the buyer app to provide the phone number to the seller app for establishing a secure connection by the seller app through third party applications like Ameyo, etc. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;iii. Video consultation: Where the astrologer consults on a video call with the buyer. The video chat room link would be passed through the protocol to the buyer app where the buyer would be redirected. </p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;iv. In- Progress: astro consultation service is in progress</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;3. Completed: When the astrology service is completed</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;iii. As and when actual delivery is completed for the Puja service ,buyer app to send completed to mark the delivery completion of the puja service</p><p>&emsp;c. Scenario 3: Fulfilment Type- Video</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. If the buyer app fails to provide order completion status at the time of service completion, the seller app can make an unsolicited status call to get an update regarding the status of consultation.</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;i. Scenario 1: Consultation incomplete</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;1. User did not join the consultation</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;b. Astrologer did not join the consultation</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;c. Time out error</p><p>&emsp;&emsp;ii. Scenario 2: If the consultation is successfully completed by then, buyer app to update the status to seller app</p><p></p> |
